Data  Access  in an MVC  Application
1.Install  EF.
2.Add  EmployeeContext.cs    class file to the model Folder.
3.Add  a  Connection String to  the  web.config  file, in the root directory.
4.Map  “Employee”  model   class  to the  database  table,  tblEmployee  using  “Table” attribute.
5.required Changes   to “Details” Action Method in “EmployeeController”.
6.in  Global.asax  file  turn off database  initialization.
     
